  "text": "To determine IRE1 cleavage sites in Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs, we performed 5 rapid amplification of cDNA ends (RACE) PCR on in vitro-transcribed mRNAs after IRE1 cleavage. This procedure identified one cleavage site in Cyp1a2 and four sites in Cyp2e1 mRNAs (Fig. 8 D) . DNA sequencing of PCR products revealed that IRE1 cleaves at G-C junctions within 5CUGCAG3 consensus sequences, which are conserved in XBP1 and in other RIDD substrate mRNAs [CITATION_1] . Although secondary ",
